title: PML-N candidate Barkat Ali wins PB-27 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz’s candidate Barkat Ali won the Balochistan Assembly election from PB-27, Kech by securing 15,552 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was independent candidate Jameel Ahmed Dashti who bagged 4,622 votes.
Overall voters’ turnout remained 45.360 percent.
